@NODE "ToggleStat" "ToggleStat"
@TOC "MAIN"
                           4.2.10 Toggle Status
                           ********************

This Button has many features:


                           @{" Start   " LINK "Start"} a Node
                           @{" Expand  " LINK "Exp"} a Node
                           @{" Iconify " LINK "Iconify"} a Node


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Start" "Start"
@TOC "MAIN"

Start a Node:
-------------

Activate a "Offline" node in the Window-1.

Select this Button (Toggle Status) and the selected node will start up.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Exp" "Exp"
@TOC "MAIN"

Expand:
-------

A Node in the  Window-1 is selected and is now iconified.

When useing this Button "Toggle Status", this node will get expanded.



@ENDNODE

@NODE "Iconify" "Iconify"
@TOC "MAIN"

Iconifing:
----------

If  any  Node  in Window-1 is selected and the Node is expanded this Button
will iconify the Node.



@ENDNODE

@NODE "LoadData" "LoadData"
@TOC "MAIN"
                           4.2.11 Load BBS-Data
                           ********************

This function loads the datas from the configuration you have defined with
your BBSConfig for the selected Node.

Note: This function need to have a selected Node on Window-1



@ENDNODE

@NODE "BBSConf" "BBSConf"
@TOC "MAIN"
                             4.2.12 BBSConfig
                             ****************


This Button starts the BBSConfig program.  The  Node.datas of  the selected
Node  are  loaded and BBSconfig will start.  This is like running BBSConfig
from your Shell.

Note: This function need to have a selected Node on Window-1



@ENDNODE

@NODE "RestModem" "RestModem"
@TOC "MAIN"
                            4.2.13 Reset Modem
                            ******************

This function resets your Modem and loads the defined datas from your Setup
Directory for the selected node.

Note: This function need to have a selected Node on Window-1



@ENDNODE

@NODE "NewShell" "NewShell"
@TOC "MAIN"
                             4.2.14 New Shell
                             ****************

This  will  start  a  new  Shell-Task.   It needs that you have defined the
"NewShell" with your BBSConfig (Open Local Shell). 

Read the BBSConfig-Document.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "EAE" "EAE"
@TOC "MAIN"
                                4.2.15 EAE
                                **********

This  Button  loads the EAE (External Account Editor).  Its like running it
from your Shell. 

If failed loading check the  @{" ToolTypes " LINK "TT"} .

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Quit" "Quit"
@TOC "MAIN"
Quit

                                4.2.16 Quit
                                ***********

This will exit the Tempest Master Server. Just press the close-gadget.

Sometimes  it happens that the TMS didn't quit.  This will be if the TMS is
waiting  for  an  answer  from  one of the running nodes or other programs.
This is no error or bug!

After answering this "msgCmds" the TMS will exit itself.



@ENDNODE

@NODE "KeyContr" "KeyContr"
@TOC "MAIN"
                           4.3 Keyboard control
                           ********************
                
If the Window of the Tempest Master Server is activ you can use the HotKeys 
that are shown on the Gadgets (Underlined characters).



@ENDNODE

